dct_title_s: West Fork White River : junction East and West Forks to Indianapolis, Ind. : chart 30 to chart 53 inclusive
dct_description_sm: Surveyed and mapped under the direction of The United States Engineer Office, Louisville, Ky. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings. "War Department"--Upper left corner of each sheet. "This survey was made by use of aerial photography, plane table stadia, chained transit traverse control and second order vertical control. Aerial photography was begun August 21st and completed October 12, 1930."  Includes index map on charts 32, 42, 45, 46, 49, 52.
Dimensions: 92 x 97 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:12,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers. Louisville District
